The paper deals with detecting anomalous events in IP traffic, which is a topic related to network security and intrusion detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Security and Privacy). The paper also uses the link stream formalism to capture temporal and structural features of the data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to detect outliers and identify their cause in a sequence of similar heterogeneous distributions, which could be relevant to the categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper applies the method to several MAWI captures of IP traffic, which involves data analysis and machine learning techniques, potentially fitting with cs.LG (Machine Learning).
